    "narrative": "Ghost Ride the WHIP leans into speed and favorable park factors today, headlined by **Corbin Carroll** (87.14) and **James Wood** (78.42). **Corbin Carroll** is our premier start; he faces a favorable 4.47 xERA arm in a spot bolstered by a \"slow delivery\" indicator that significantly enhances his stolen base probability\u2014our league\u2019s scarcest commodity. Joining him as a high-leverage target is **Mickey Moniak** (75.75). He benefits from an elite 14% boost via platoon advantage against V\u00e1squez, and his slotting in the #2 hole ensures maximum opportunities to capitalize on a hitter-friendly venue. Meanwhile, **Brice Turang** (72.86) and **Trevor Story** (72.05) remain locked in due to high SP skill ratings and positive park factors, providing a reliable floor for our daily efficiency targets.\n\nOur most difficult decision centered on the utility spot, where **Vinnie Pasquantino** (72.01) held off **Alex Freeland** (49.73) and **Giancarlo Stanton** (49.27). While **Alex Freeland** offers switch-hitting versatility, his #9 spot in the order severely capped his ceiling, and he carries the same 42% rain risk that shadows **Dalton Rushing**. Speaking of **Dalton Rushing**, he is our riskiest active play; despite a decent score of 56.46, the inclement weather in his matchup forces us to monitor for late-afternoon postponement. Elsewhere, **Jose Caballero** (51.18) remains a necessary evil despite the brutal 2.34 xERA matchup against Early, as his dynamic platoon edge and speed profile outweigh the bench alternatives like **Jazz Chisholm Jr.**, whose recent struggles against southpaws resulted in a marginal 46.05 score. With **Max Muncy** (46.04) benched to maintain our game cap integrity, we are prioritizing high-OBP, high-speed profiles to maximize our 5x5 rotation.",
